 :tx/rationale "Create task: EPIC: Topology as Compilation — Coupling Density Matrix and Spectral Agent Assignment (ADR-TOPOLOGY-004, INV-TOPOLOGY-004, INV-TOPOLOGY-005, spec/19-topology.md, spec/20-coherence.md). BACKGROUND: The Coupling-Coherence Isomorphism establishes that the normalized coupling matrix rho_C = C/Tr(C) IS a density matrix whose von Neumann entropy S(rho_C) equals the irreducible coordination complexity of the task portfolio. Spectral decomposition of rho_C determines optimal topology: eigenvalues = coupling strengths along principal directions, eigenvectors = independent task clusters, effective rank r_eff = exp(S) = optimal number of parallel agent groups. This unifies topology (coordination) with coherence (verification) through a single algebraic object. All required mathematical infrastructure exists in query/graph.rs (eigendecomposition, Fiedler, Cheeger, von Neumann entropy, persistent homology). This EPIC implements the full compilation pipeline: front-end (coupling extraction), middle-end (spectral partition + CALM classify), back-end (topology plan emission), and PGO (harvest-time refinement). Traces to ADR-TOPOLOGY-004 (topology as compilation), INV-TOPOLOGY-004 (composite coupling signal), INV-TOPOLOGY-005 (coupling-to-topology determinism), INV-COHERENCE-001 (density matrix axioms)."
